      "Description": "This lesson explores how artificial intelligence is being used across the hospitality industry and the privacy risks it introduces when handling sensitive guest information. You will learn how AI systems collect, process, and store personal, travel, and payment data, and why this creates new responsibilities for hospitality professionals. We will look at common scenarios where guest data can be exposed or misused, and how to recognise the warning signs. By the end of this lesson, you will have a clear understanding of the practical steps you can take to help protect guest privacy and ensure your organisation handles data in a responsible and compliant way.",
